Sprint Corp (S) Files 10-K for the Fiscal Year Ended on March 31, 2017


May 26, 2017, 12:48:06 PM EDT
By insider, GuruFocus









































Shutterstock photo


Sprint Corp ( S ) files its latest 10-K with SEC for the fiscal year ended on March 31, 2017. Sprint Corp is a communications company offering wireless and wireline communications products and services to individual consumers, businesses, government subscribers and resellers. Sprint Corp has a market cap of $33.45 billion; its shares were traded at around $8.39 with and P/S ratio of 1.01. Sprint Corp had annual average EBITDA growth of 17.80% over the past five years.For the last quarter Sprint Corp reported a revenue of $8.5 billion, compared with the revenue of $8.1 billion during the same period a year ago. For the latest fiscal year the company reported a revenue of $33.3 billion, an increase of 3.6% from last year. For the last five years Sprint Corp had an average revenue growth rate of 1.1% a year.The reported loss per diluted share was 30 cents for the year, compared with the loss per share of $1.44 in the previous year. The Sprint Corp had an operating margin of 5.29%, compared with the operating margin of 0.96% a year before. The 10-year historical median operating margin of Sprint Corp is -4.74%. The profitability rank of the company is 4 (out of 10).At the end of the fiscal year, Sprint Corp has the cash and cash equivalents of $2.9 billion, compared with $2.6 billion in the previous year. The long term debt was $35.9 billion, compared with $29.3 billion in the previous year. The company's operating income of cannot cover its interest payment during the last fiscal year. Sprint Corp has a financial strength rank of 4 (out of 10).At the current stock price of $8.39, Sprint Corp is traded at 96.5% premium to its historical median P/S valuation band of $4.27 . The P/S ratio of the stock is 1.01, while the historical median P/S ratio is 0.51. The stock gained 135.98% during the past 12 months.click here.

About GuruFocus: GuruFocus.com tracks the stocks picks and portfolio holdings of the world's best investors. This value investing site offers stock screeners and valuation tools. And publishes daily articles tracking the latest moves of the world's best investors. GuruFocus also provides promising stock ideas in 3 monthly newsletters sent to Premium Members . 

This article first appeared on GuruFocus .



The views and opinions expressed herein are the views and opinions of the author and do not necessarily reflect those of Nasdaq, Inc.











